Helper Function (make_request_with_retry):

This function handles the retry logic, including exponential backoff with jitter.
It takes a request_func as an argument, which allows us to pass different request methods (e.g., requests.post, requests.put).
Integration in do_post and do_put:

We define a request_func within do_post and do_put that calls the respective requests method.
We call make_request_with_retry with the request_func to handle the retry logic.
By integrating the retry logic in this manner, you ensure that the existing functionality and structure of your do_post and do_put functions remain unchanged, while adding the desired retry behavior. This approach minimizes changes to the existing codebase, reducing the risk of introducing new issues.


